    <h1 class="opener__hed  opener__hed--small" >        He Fled a Traffic Stop in Louisiana. Now He’s in Prison for Life.
    </h1>

    
            <div class="article-meta-1 ">
            <span class="article-meta-1__byline">
                by <span class="name">Richard A. Webster</span>, <a href="https://veritenews.org/">Verite News</a>            </span>
            <time class="article-meta-1__pubdate">
                <time class="timestamp" datetime="2023-09-08EDT07:00">Sept. 8, 7 a.m. EDT</time>
            </time>
        </div>
    
    </div> <!-- Close .opener__topic-title-dek-wrapper -->

        <div class="content"> <!-- not sure if this is the best way to reestablish the text column -->
        <h2 class="opener__dek opener__dek--match-text-column" >            After 12 years behind bars, Markus Lanieux thought he had a deal for his release. Then Louisiana Attorney General Jeff Landry filed a legal challenge that could derail hope for those imprisoned under the state&#039;s &quot;three strikes&quot; sentencing rules.
        </h2>
    </div>
    
</div>
        
<div class="article-meta-1
